column1: # Information about Gene and IDs from Ecocyc and GenBank
# - GENE_POSLEFT:    Absolute genome left position of the gene
# - GENE_POSRIGHT:   Absolute genome right position of the gene
# - GENE_TYPE:       Type of the gene [ gene, pseudo gene, phantom gene]
#  The totals and the unix commands using this data file is indicated.
#   Data File lines: 4739         ```grep -v '^#' GeneProduct-IDs.txt |grep ECK12 | wc -l ```
#   Total of genes:        4739   ```grep -v '^#' GeneProduct-IDs.txt | cut -f1 | grep ECK12 | wc -l```
#   Genes without Ecocyc ID: 29   ```grep -v '^#' GeneProduct-IDs.txt | cut -f2 | grep -e  "-$" | wc -l```
#   Genes without bnumber:   84   ```grep -v '^#' GeneProduct-IDs.txt | cut -f3 | grep -e  "-$" | wc -l```
#   Gene Type Totals     :        ```grep -v '^#' GeneProduct-IDs.txt | cut -f9 | sort | uniq -c```
#   Genes with more than one product:
#   ```grep -v '^#' GeneProduct-IDs.txt |grep ECK12 | cut -f1 | sort | uniq -c | sort -nr | cut -c1-5 | sort | uniq -c```
#        4726    1     4725 genes with 1 product  ( 94 of them have not product)
#    ```grep -v '^#' GeneProduct-IDs.txt |grep ECK12 | perl -ne 'chomp; @F=split(/\t/,$_); if ($F[9] eq "-") { print "$F[0] $F[3] $F[8] $F[9]\n";} ' |wc```
#     ```grep -v '^#' GeneProduct-IDs.txt |grep ECK12 | perl -ne 'chomp; @F=split(/\t/,$_); if ($F[12] eq "small RNA") { print "$F[0]\t$F[3]\t$F[12]\n";} |wc’```

#  * Some genes have no BNumber because the genes reported in the papers are not included in the Genbank File
#  * Some genes have more than one product
#  * The small RNA from the RegulonDB collaborator are marked as “small RNA” in the product type
